               <head>Miscellaneous court reports</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Akhbār</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85033556 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009117885 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010109514 http://lccn.loc.gov/n2009200816 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111662" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4345-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Miscellaneous reports or akhbār on events and transactions at several courts, including 1) the Timurid or Mughal <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657054.0x000001 viaf_308694679" role="subject">Emperor Akbar Shāh II</persName>’s imperial court at <placeName>Delhi</placeName> and government of India, entitled <title>Akhbār-i darbār-i muqaddas-i muʿallá</title>, 2) the Maratha court of <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658569.0x000001 viaf_61179473" role="subject">Jasvant Rao Holkar</persName>, entitled <title>Muntakhab-i akhbār</title>, 3) the Maratha armies of <persName key="viaf_61179473" role="subject">Jasvant Rao Holkar</persName>, entitled <title>Akhbār-i lashkar</title>, 4) the Rajput court of <persName key="person_f7502" role="subject">Rao (Rajah) Sivai Jai Singh</persName>, entitled <title>Akhbār-i dyūdhī</title>, 5) the Sikh court of <persName key="person_f7517" role="subject">Sardar (Maharajah) Ranjit Singh</persName>, entitled <title>Akhbār-i dyūdhī</title>, and 6) the Rajput court of <persName key="person_f7615" role="subject">Sivai Jagat Singh</persName>, also entitled <title>Akhbār-i dyūdhī</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Accounts partially cover the period from 23 Ramaz̤ān 1224/2 November 1809 to 22 Muḥarram regnal year 5 (=1226)/17 February 1811 </p>
                        <p>English note at end (f. 49v): Hydenham (?) Resident, <placeName>Hydrabad</placeName> 26th November 1809 
Accounts additionally dated on reverse (recto face) with Gregorian dates 
                        </p>
                        <p>Accounts on single leaves and scrolls mounted in volume in English order, with each news or khabar leaf beginning on the verso side and mounted in reverse, yet unsystematic, date order, the first folio being the latest khabar and the last (f. 49) being the earliest </p>
                        <p>Bundles of akhbār constituting sets of dispatches mounted as clusters along upper or lower edges </p>
                        <p>Pencil annotations throughout 
</p>
                        <p>Small Indian taʿlīq </p>
                        <p>Date of compilation not recorded </p>
                     </note>
